      "quality_value": 0.1,
      "timestep_posted": 4
    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_7_listing_7",
      "firm_id": "sybil_7",
      "description": "Presenting an investment-grade 2004 BMW M3 (E46) Coupe, a definitive example of high-revving naturally aspirated engineering. At its heart lies the S54 3.2L inline-six, featuring individual throttle bodies and a double-VANOS variable valve timing system that pulls cleanly to its 8,000 RPM redline. This chassis has undergone proactive subframe reinforcement and a comprehensive rod bearing service, addressing the critical mechanical milestones of the platform. Power is managed via a tactile Getrag 6-speed manual transmission and a GKN variable M-differential, ensuring optimal torque distribution. The vehicle retains its original factory geometry with a pristine suspension setup and zero signs of oxidation on the undercarriage. Finished in its original paint with a flawless interior, this specimen represents a rare opportunity to own a mechanically synchronized and aesthetically preserved icon of the M-division.",
      "price": 48500.0,
